<title>USA: BEFORE THE BELL - Comcast, cable cos firm.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL - Comcast, cable cos firm.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Comcast Corp shares traded higher preceding Monday's U.S. market open as investors bought into Microsoft Corp's agreement to invest $1 billion in the cable televsion company, traders said.</p>
<p>Before the opening bell, Comcast shares rose to 21 from 18-1/4, traders said.</p>
<p>Also, Tele-Communications Inc, the nation's largest cable operator, firmed to 16 from 15-1/16 after it said it agreed to sell ten of its cable systems to Cablevision Systems Corp for 12.2 million Cablevision shares.</p>
